defaultAdverse weather
default - weather that is bad but not unusual
default. In winter the definitions include more than 2cm of snow in 
defaultLondon
default and the southeast or 5cm elsewhere with a warning about accumulation or drift risk, 60mph winds or temperatures below -3ºC. 
defaultAll
default normal
default years have periods of adverse weather. 
defaultDuring adverse weather the 
defaultindustry plans to run a full service but punctuality may be a fe
defaultw PPM points lower than 
defaulton a normal day
default;
default&#xa0;
defaultExtreme weather
default - rare weather that is seen once every ten or twenty years
default. In winter this is defined as more than 15cm snow, 70mph winds and temperatures below -7
default 
defaultºC. 
defaultDuring extreme weather the industry seeks to ensure all
default 
defaultcustomer journeys are completed safely
default, and punctuality is not prioritised. 
